.TH mailq "" "" Command
.PC "Display information about spooled mail"
\fBmailq [\-v]
.PP
Command
.B mailq
displays information about the mail currently spooled in directory
.B /usr/spool/mail
and its sub-directories.
Command-line option
.B \-v
tells
.B mailq
to display a per-message transaction log for each message, which shows
what has happened to the message so far.
.SH "See Also"
.Xr "commands," commands
.Xr "mail [overview]," mail.o
.Xr "smail" smail
.SH Notes
.B mailq
is a link to command
.BR smail .
